#3: Set the tone at the top.¬†"Building a culture of flexibility and balance only works if employees feel empowered to use it. That's why your leadership team needs to be leading from the front. It's critical we're normalizing unplugging and mental health by walking the walk."

#2: Prioritize deep work.¬†"Jumping from Zoom meetings to Slack to email barely leaves time for lunch, let alone productivity. That's why we adopted a 'No Internal Meeting Fridays' rule. We're creating space for our employees and leaders to do deep work."

#1: Be vulnerable with your customers.¬†"Before HubSpot's annual 'Week of Rest', we proactively communicated to our customers why we were taking time off. Our customers were thrilled ... When [they] invest in your product, they're investing in your people, too."
